black hole in the equatorial\nplane has different behaviour for different $\\alpha$ and the black hole spin\n$a$. It is asymptotically flat and independent of $\\alpha$ if $\\alpha>0$ while\nis asymptotically flat only when $\\alpha$ is close to zero if $\\alpha<0$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Nov 2017 11:53:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Apr 2018 02:02:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-24"}
