n\n(IMF) and extrapolating the stellar IMF down to lower masses, we determine a\nstar formation rate (SFR) of ~0.046 +/- 0.026 Msun/yr assuming an average age\nof 0.75 +/- 0.25 Myr for the YSOs. This value is lower than estimates found\nusing the YSO counting method in the literature. Our SFR estimate in the CMZ\nagrees with the previous estimates from different methods and reaffirms that\nstar formation in the CMZ is proceeding at a lower rate than predicted by\nvarious star forming models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Nov 2017 12:35:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-07"}
