 the pair-distribution function is non-negligible\nall around the reference particle indicating that there is a substantial amount\nof clustering at radial distances between 2 and $6c$ (with $c$ the polar radius\nof the oblate).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Nov 2017 14:19:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-01"}
